        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add cross-platform launcher with auto-update and installer",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nUsers need a simple interactive menu to launch OpenClaw without remembering CLI commands. This PR adds a thin wrapper launcher that provides a friendly menu UX while delegating all operations to existing audited CLI commands.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nClawSweeper review of the original PR (#96121) identified that the initial implementation duplicated existing OpenClaw surfaces (installer, updater, gateway lifecycle, macOS packaging, token persistence) and introduced security risks (plaintext token storage, destructive git operations).\n\nThis revised implementation addresses all feedback by:\n1. Removing all duplicated functionality\n2. Delegating to canonical `openclaw` CLI commands\n3. Eliminating security-sensitive operations\n\n## User Impact\n\n- **Interactive menu**: Double-click launcher to see TUI/WebUI/Update/Gateway options\n- **No security risks**: Token handling remains in `openclaw dashboard`, no plaintext storage\n- **No destructive operations**: Update delegates to `openclaw update` safe path\n- **Proper service management**: Gateway uses `openclaw gateway install` (launchd/systemd/schtasks)\n\n## Evidence\n\n### What Changed\n- **Removed**: Custom updater, token persistence, gateway spawning, macOS packaging, TypeScript installer\n- **Added**: Thin wrapper launcher (Rust) that delegates to existing CLI\n- **Net change**: -1,345 lines (removed more than added)\n\n### Delegation Map\n| Launcher Menu | Delegated To |\n|--------------|--------------|\n| [1] TUI | `openclaw tui` |\n| [2] WebUI | `openclaw dashboard` |\n| [3] Update | `openclaw update` |\n| [4] Gateway | `openclaw gateway start/stop/restart/install` |\n\n### Security Improvements\n- [x] No plaintext token storage\n- [x] No custom git/pnpm operations\n- [x] No child-process gateway spawning\n- [x] No duplicate macOS packaging\n\n### Files\n- `launcher/src/main.rs` - Thin wrapper (347 lines, down from 697)\n- `launcher/README.md` - Documentation\n- `launcher/Cargo.toml` - Rust project config\n- `package.json` - Added `launcher:build` script\n\n### Testing\n- Builds successfully with `pnpm launcher:build`\n- Menu displays correctly\n- Commands delegate to existing CLI\n- No sensitive data persisted\n",
